{"id":14881930,"mediaExerciseId":"83e1aeb3-6410-41df-a68f-8f887b55b327","exerciseName":"12","chapterName":"25","chapterTitle":"Option Valuation","groupId":612508,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":857,"solutions":[{"id":6515775,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise,  we are going to learn about put-call parity. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"To start with, let's define put-call parity. \n\nA **put-call parity** is the correlation between a call and put option which is connected on the same underlying futures contract. This option contract has the same exercise price, expiration date, and asset. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"The equation of put call parity is illustrated below: \n\n$$\\text{S}+\\text{P}=\\text{X}(\\text{E})^{\\text{rt}}+\\text{C}$$\n\nWhere: \n\n- S - Current price of the stock\n- PV - Present value of strike price\n- P - Put option\n- C - Call option\n- r - Risk-free rate\n- t - Time\n\nThe sum of the stock price and put option is equal to the sum of the present value of the strike price and call option. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"Here are the parameters to solve the requirement : \n\n|Given | | \n|--|--| \n|Call option (C)|$2.75 | \n|Exercise price of the call option (X)|$25 | \n|e | 2.71828| \n| Risk-free rate (r) |2.5% | \n|Time (t) |4 months;4/12;0.3333 | \n|Stock Price (S) |$23.80 | \n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"Now, using the equation in Step 3, the price of the put option is solved below: \n\n&nbsp;\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\$23.80+\\textbf{P}&=[(\\$25)(2.71828)^{-(0.025)(0.33)}]+\\$2.75\\\\[10pt]\n\\$23.80+\\textbf{P}&=[(\\$25)(2.71828)^{-0.00825}]+\\$2.75\\\\[10pt]\n\\$23.80+\\textbf{P}&=[(\\$25)(0.9918)]+\\$2.75\\\\[10pt]\n\\$23.80+\\textbf{P}&=\\$24.80+\\$2.75\\\\[10pt]\n\\$23.80+\\textbf{P}&=\\$27.55\\\\[10pt]\n\\textbf{P}&=\\$27.55-\\$23.80\\\\[10pt]\n\\textbf{P}&=\\boxed{\\$3.75}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nTherefore, the price of the put option is $3.75. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"a26b4cea-e748-4b1f-b182-45f2662a11ed","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":5}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881931,"exerciseName":"13","page":857,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"55d0cd98-741d-4b0e-bea5-7d0c4efebcca","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-25-questions-and-problems-13-55d0cd98-741d-4b0e-bea5-7d0c4efebcca"},{"id":14881932,"exerciseName":"14","page":857,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"282eb5ba-0b6e-419d-a7e7-d5ec7d169719","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter